---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services & pricing"
  description="One clearly defined website package for local service businesses: 3–5 mobile-first pages, local SEO foundations, accessible build, and full ownership. Founding-client pricing from $1,200."
>
  <header class="page-intro container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Services</p>
    <h1>One package, clearly defined</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      I offer a single, tightly scoped website package instead of a menu of
      vague options. You'll know exactly what's included, what isn't, and
      what it costs — in writing — before anything starts.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="section container" aria-labelledby="included-heading">
    <div class="section-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">The package</p>
      <h2 id="included-heading">The local business website</h2>
      <p>
        A lead-generation website of three to five focused pages — typically
        Home, Services, About, and Contact, plus a service-area or FAQ page
        when it earns its place.
      </p>
    </div>
    <dl class="spec-list">
      <div>
        <dt>Mobile-first design</dt>
        <dd>
          Designed for the phone screen first, because that's where most of
          your customers will see it — then refined for tablets and desktops.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Fast, lightweight pages</dt>
        <dd>
          Hand-built static pages with no heavyweight page builders or plugin
          stacks, hosted on Cloudflare's global network.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Clear calls to action</dt>
        <dd>
          Every page guides an interested visitor toward contacting you —
          call, email, or quote request.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Local SEO foundations</dt>
        <dd>
          Descriptive page titles, meta descriptions, a sitemap, clean URLs,
          and consistent business details that search engines can read. Solid
          groundwork — not a ranking guarantee, because no honest person can
          promise rankings.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Accessibility-conscious build</dt>
        <dd>
          Readable contrast, keyboard-friendly navigation, and properly
          structured pages, so more customers can actually use your site.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Content shaping</dt>
        <dd>
          You know your trade; I help turn that knowledge into clear page
          copy. You review and approve every word before launch.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Launch and handoff</dt>
        <dd>
          Deployment to fast hosting, a walkthrough of how everything works,
          and written documentation. The domain, code, and content are yours.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Defined revisions</dt>
        <dd>
          Two structured revision rounds are built into the project, so
          feedback has a clear place and the project actually finishes.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="section container" aria-labelledby="excluded-heading">
    <div class="section-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Scope honesty</p>
      <h2 id="excluded-heading">What's deliberately not included</h2>
      <p>
        A narrow scope is why the price is fixed and the quality is
        consistent. If you need these, I'll say so up front and point you in
        the right direction rather than improvise.
      </p>
    </div>
    <dl class="spec-list">
      <div>
        <dt>Online stores</dt>
        <dd>Ecommerce, carts, and payment processing are out of scope.</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Booking systems &amp; portals</dt>
        <dd>
          Customer accounts, login areas, and scheduling platforms need
          different tooling than this package provides.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Custom web applications</dt>
        <dd>No custom backends, databases, or complex content systems.</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Logo and brand design</dt>
        <dd>
          I'll present your existing logo and colors well, but original brand
          design is a different craft.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Ranking or lead guarantees</dt>
        <dd>
          I build the site right and set solid foundations. Anyone promising
          you a specific Google position or lead volume is guessing — or
          worse.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="section container" id="pricing" aria-labelledby="pricing-heading">
    <div class="section-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h2 id="pricing-heading">Fixed quotes, stated plainly</h2>
      <p>
        Every project gets a written fixed quote before work begins. These
        ranges are where quotes land depending on page count and content
        readiness.
      </p>
    </div>
    <dl class="spec-list">
      <div>
        <dt>Founding-client projects</dt>
        <dd>
          <strong>$1,200–$1,500.</strong> I'm early in building this service,
          and my first clients take a chance on someone newer to client work.
          The founding rate reflects that honestly — same process and care as
          the standard rate.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Standard projects</dt>
        <dd>
          <strong>$1,800–$2,500</strong> once the founding phase ends. If you
          hire me at the founding rate, that's your price — it won't be
          revised upward mid-project.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Payment terms</dt>
        <dd>
          50% deposit to schedule the project, remainder at launch. No
          surprise line items.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Optional care plan</dt>
        <dd>
          A small monthly plan covering updates and content changes within a
          defined allowance, for owners who'd rather not touch the site
          themselves. Details and pricing provided with your quote — never
          required.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="btn" href="/contact/">Request a quote</a>
      <a class="btn secondary" href="/process/">How delivery works</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
